{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17610241","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17610241"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:57:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:57:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16144"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16144","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16144"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.73,0.02,0.11,0.07,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8835"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64073"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8835","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8835"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16144"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49504"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"9861"},{"type":"tags","id":"9872"},{"type":"tags","id":"10623"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21068"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21071"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64073","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/64073"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring pregnancy, significant cardiovascular adaptations occur to meet the increased metabolic demands of both mother and fetus.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a cardiovascular parameter that is reduced during normal pregnancy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Systemic vascular resistance","Cardiac output","Stroke volume","Heart rate","Blood volume"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring normal pregnancy, \u003Cstrong\u003Esystemic vascular resistance\u003C/strong\u003E decreases due to the vasodilatory effects of progesterone and other factors. This leads to a physiological reduction in blood pressure, particularly during the first and second trimesters.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other cardiovascular parameters all increase to support the growing demands of pregnancy:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECardiac output\u003C/strong\u003E increases by 30-50%\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStroke volume\u003C/strong\u003E increases by about 30%\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHeart rate\u003C/strong\u003E increases by 10-20 beats per minute\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlood volume\u003C/strong\u003E increases by 30-50%\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese changes help ensure adequate perfusion of maternal organs and the developing fetus despite the reduction in vascular resistance.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Normal pregnancy causes physiological reduction in blood pressure due to systemic vasodilation, despite increased cardiac output.","Cardiac output, stroke volume, and heart rate all increase during normal pregnancy to meet increased metabolic demands."],"references":["Braunthal S, Brateanu A. Hypertension in pregnancy: Pathophysiology and treatment. SAGE Open Med. 2019 Apr 10;7:2050312119843700. doi: 10.1177/2050312119843700. PMID: 31007914; PMCID: PMC6458675.","Soma-Pillay P, Nelson-Piercy C, Tolppanen H, Mebazaa A. Physiological changes in pregnancy. Cardiovasc J Afr. 2016 Mar-Apr;27(2):89-94. doi: 10.5830/CVJA-2016-021. PMID: 27213856; PMCID: PMC4928162","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49504"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16144"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49504","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/49504"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-22T21:55:11+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-22T21:55:35+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8835"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64073"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4926","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4926"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiovascular","synonyms":[],"d